      '\n' +
      "Copilot CLI doesn't resolve transitive deps; install both explicitly.\n" +
      '\n' +
      '### Under Ouroboros\n' +
      '\n' +
      '```bash\n' +
      'ouro plugin install ourostack/ouroboros-skills:plugins/desk --agent <agent-name>\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '\n' +
      "The agent's `bundle.json` gains a `plugins[]` entry; the agent's preamble declares `Your desk: ~/AgentBundles/<agent>.ouro/desk/`.\n" +
      '\n' +
      '### Under Claude Code\n' +
      '\n' +
      'The `ourostack/ouroboros-skills` repo ships a Claude Code marketplace manifest at `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`, so installation is two slash commands inside a Claude Code session:\n' +
      '\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '/plugin marketplace add ourostack/ouroboros-skills\n' +
      '/plugin install desk@ouroboros-skills\n' +
      '/plugin install work-suite@ouroboros-skills\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '\n' +
      "Claude Code doesn't auto-resolve plugin deps — install `work-suite` explicitly (it provides the doing-phase skills the desk agent references).\n" +
      '\n' +
      'After install, launch the default worker agent:\n' +
      '\n' +
      '```bash\n' +
      'claude --agent desk:worker\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '\n' +
      "Or inside an existing Claude session: `@desk:worker say hi`. The agent's preamble auto-loads with the cozy library voice and a placeholder `$DESK` binding (typically `~/desk/`). See [`docs/agent-files.md`](./docs/agent-files.md) for the full agent file reference.\n" +
      '\n' +
      '### Under Codex\n' +
      '\n' +
      'The plugin ships a `.codex-plugin/plugin.json` manifest and a companion `work-suite` plugin manifest. For a home-local install, copy both plugin directories into `~/plugins/`, expose them through a local marketplace rooted at `~/.agents/plugins/marketplace.json`, then enable both plugins from `~/.codex/config.toml`.\n' +
      '\n' +
      'Minimum local setup:\n' +
      '\n' +
      '```bash\n' +
      'mkdir -p ~/plugins\n' +
      'rsync -a --delete /path/to/ouroboros-skills/plugins/desk/ ~/plugins/desk/\n' +
      'rsync -a --delete /path/to/ouroboros-skills/plugins/work-suite/ ~/plugins/work-suite/\n' +
      'cd ~/plugins/desk/mcp && npm install\n' +
      'codex mcp add desk -- node "$HOME/plugins/desk/mcp/index.js" --root "$HOME/desk"\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '\n' +
      'Then add a local Codex marketplace entry whose source is `$HOME`, enable `desk@<marketplace-name>` and `work-suite@<marketplace-name>`, and restart Codex so newly installed skills and MCP tools are loaded.\n' +
      '\n' +
      'For semantic search, keep Ollama reachable with `nomic-embed-text` pulled. The MCP honors `OLLAMA_HOST` plus `DESK_EMBED_ENDPOINT` / `DESK_EMBED_MODEL` overrides, and `desk_reindex` without arguments repairs any lexical-only index once embeddings are reachable.\n' +
      '\n' +
      'See `desk:codex-onboarding` for the repair checklist and verification steps.\n' +
      '\n' +
      '## Invocation — the default `worker` agent\n' +
      '\n' +
      "The plugin ships a substrate-default agent named `worker` — a long-running engineering agent that uses the desk (tracks, tasks, friction, lessons) to keep its work coherent across sessions. It's standalone-functional; you don't need to author a consumer overlay to start working.\n" +
      '\n' +
      '```bash\n' +
      '# Claude Code (via plugin loader / marketplace)\n' +
      'claude --agent desk:worker\n' +
      '\n' +
      '# Copilot CLI\n' +
      'copilot --agent worker\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '\n' +
      '**Codex — two paths**. Codex plugins cannot ship agents or AGENTS.md content directly per the plugin schema, so the agent layer is user-installed. Pick one or both:\n' +
      '\n' +
      '```bash\n' +
      '# Path A — default behavior (recommended): make Codex itself behave like worker\n' +
      '# every session by appending the canonical body to ~/.codex/AGENTS.md.\n' +
      "awk '/^---$/{c++; next} c>=2' ~/plugins/desk/agents/worker.md >> ~/.codex/AGENTS.md\n" +
      '\n' +
      '# Path B — explicit subagent: invoke /agent worker on demand\n' +
      'cp ~/plugins/desk/agents/worker.toml ~/.codex/agents/worker.toml\n' +
      '# then in a Codex session: /agent worker\n' +
      '```\n' +
      '\n' +
      'Paths A and B compose. See [`docs/agent-files.md`](./docs/agent-files.md) for the per-harness install reference, and `desk:codex-onboarding` for the full Codex install sequence including the agent layer.\n' +
      '\n' +
      "Three agent files (`agents/worker.md`, `agents/worker.agent.md`, `agents/worker.toml`) ship the same canonical body in each harness's expected format. If you want a context-specific overlay (corporate-engineering, autonomous-agent, personal-coding), author it as a sibling plugin that depends on `desk` and provides its own agent file; the substrate stays generic.\n" +
      '\n' +
      '## what desk gives an agent\n' +
      '\n' +
      'a furnished room, ready to settle into. the layout, the lifecycle, the small ceremonies for tending it.\n' +
      '\n' +
      '### workspace structure\n' +
      '- `$DESK/<track>/<task>/<iteration>/` — drawers, folders inside drawers, pages laid open one per work session\n' +
      '- `track.md` and `task.md` cards as canonical state (frontmatter + body)\n' +
      '- `$DESK/_meta/`, `$DESK/_archive/`, `$DESK/_friction/`, `$DESK/_planning/` system directories\n' +
      '- per-iteration `planning.md` + `doing.md` + `feedback.md` (work-suite native)\n' +
      '\n' +
      '### lifecycle\n' +
      '- 8-state machine: drafting → processing → validating → collaborating → paused → blocked → done → cancelled. every task moves; some pause along the way\n' +
      '- checkpoint-type annotations on each transition (GATE / CHECKPOINT / AUTO / CONFIRM / NOTIFY)\n' +
      '- session start / resumption / archival workflow\n' +
      '\n' +
      '### dispatch\n' +
      "- `work-orchestration` routes tasks through work-suite's four phases (ideator → planner → doer → merger)\n" +
      '- non-coding workflow paths supported (execution + completion alternatives for non-code work)\n' +
      '\n' +
      '### engineering posture\n' +
      '- `evidence-discipline` — fixtures-or-refusal, smoke-before-infinity, messages-over-models, etc.\n' +
      '- `preflight-actions` — preflight pattern before irreversible actions\n' +
      '- `runtime-symptom-investigation` — narrow-the-hypothesis-space pattern for runtime issues\n' +
      '\n' +
      '### PR craft (for coding agents)\n' +
      '- `pr-self-review`, `pr-review-interrogation`, `pr-surface-hygiene` — pre-open and post-open PR discipline\n' +
      "- `peer-pr-review`, `pr-reviewer-audit` — reviewing others' code\n" +
      '\n' +
      '### friction / learning\n' +
      '- `friction-management` — pin a card to the corkboard, then encode the pattern\n' +
      "- `lesson-capture` (post-task) — mine a finished task for patterns and propose what's earned a place on the reference shelf\n" +
      '\n' +
      '## convention: the `$DESK` placeholder\n' +
      '\n' +
      "skill bodies reference workspace paths via `$DESK`, not literal paths. the host agent's preamble declares the binding — same skills, different rooms:\n" +
